 the hsbc guyerzeller business was rebranded hsbc private bank in october  hsbc private bank sold property vision holdings limited to pv acquisition limited in a  management buyout property vision was acquired by hsbc in  and specialises in managing and providing advice on property purchases property visions exit from hsbc was part of wider restructuring by the bank which made  disposals of “noncore operating assets” in  hsbc has announced  october  the transfer of the bulk of its private banking business in monaco to cfm indosuez wealth management the current hsbc private banking business houses usbn of customer assets and employs  people those assets and parts of the business that do not transfer will be wound down contents  hsbc private bank suisse  see also  references  external links hsbc private bank suisseedit hsbc private bank suisse sa was established in  as republic national bank of new york suisse sa it was the subsidiary of republic new york in  it became a part of hsbc holdings plc following the acquisition of republic new york the bank changed its name to hsbc republic bank suisse and then to hsbc private bank suisse hsbc private banking holdings suisse owns  of the bank shares and hsbc bank usa na owns the remaining shares republic new york was merged with hsbc bank usa see alsoedit swiss leaks referencesedit  primeresi december  buying agency’s  prime movers charlie ellingworth  peter mackie of property vision primeresicom   investegate  october  hsbc to sell property vision – holdings limited to management investegatecouk   primeresi december  buying agency’s  prime movers charlie ellingworth  peter mackie of property vision primeresicom   hsbc passes bulk of monaco bank to indosuez financial times  october  p external linksedit official website v t e hsbc board of directors douglas flint group chairman stuart gulliver group ceo iain mackay group finance director marc moses group chief risk officer phillip ameen kathleen l casey safra a catz laura c